title: For Sale:  When an AR-15 and PPS-43 love each other very much…
postcontent:
A rifle is born.  When an MP-40 and L1A1 somehow get into the mix, a 9mm PPS-43 with AR-15 furniture and sights with an L1A1 flash hider and bayonet are thrust upon a world both afraid and not ready for a concoction worthy only of a deep dark Soviet lab. 

Starting with a PPS-43C, the folding stock was cut off and a new production 9mm barrel added.  A flash hider from an L1A1 was welded on to obtain a minimum legal length.  A receiver extension was then crafted to allow the adjustable stock from an AR-15 to be attached which was then “crafted” into a homemade bump fire stock (no springs, etc.  = perfectly legal).  Finally, rails were added to the top to allow new sights and carry handle to be added. 

The result is the baddest, sickest, Mad Maxiest, Soviet-German-American-Britishiest mashup ever conceived by man.  Along with 5 original magazines (from which 9mm feeds beautifully), this is one serious lead spewing machine.  Add the included L1A1 bayonet and you don't even need lead to spew!

It was a project and I’m not looking to, nor do I feel I will, make a profit on it.  I’m not a manufacturer by any means so I’m just looking to move on to new toys.

With the money it takes to build something like this monster, a 1911 (Colt) or an M1 Garand would be a fair trade and I’d certainly take it but I’m open to offers.  I’m mainly seeing what kind of interest this would garner if any.  Make me an offer, any offer!

You can reply to this message but would prefer texting or calling to two70-two27-eight191.
